<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JUL 92 / Parliament and Politics: Britain to give medical help to
Sarajevo
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITAIN will give medical help to, or evacuate, children caught up in
fighting in Sarajevo, Mr Major told MPs.
The prime minister would also consider providing air cover if a land
corridor to the city could be established under United Nations' auspices. He
repeated that UK ground troops would not be sent.
However, when pressed for a pledge that the Commons would be recalled if
further British involvement was envisaged, Mr Major said: 'I would be most
unwise to give a blanket assurance to you, and I am unable to do so.'
Mr Major expects to meet the UN high commissioner for refugees later this
week.
</TEXT>
