FT  14 JUL 92 / Survey highlights tardy offices
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DIANE SUMMERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE WELSH Office and the building management section of the Property
Services Agency are the worst government departments when it comes to paying
their bills on time, according to government figures, Diane Summers writes.
Less than 42 per cent of PSA building management bills are paid within the
contract terms or 30 days. The Welsh Office, meanwhile, pays 65 per cent of
invoices within the period, according to the survey.
Top of the prompt payment league is the Inland Revenue, which pays 99 per
cent of invoices within 30 days. Other swift payers are National Savings (93
per cent) and the Department of Energy (92 per cent). The DTI itself has an
80 per cent record.
The government has recently been exhorting the private sector to help small
business suppliers, in particular, by paying bills promptly.
