FT  13 JUL 92 / Letter: When Sky's the limit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr P J R BAKER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Mr Richard Brooke's euphoria (Letters, July 7) over the recent up-beat
performance of BSkyB perhaps needs to be tempered with the realisation that
pay TV is likely to be a loser (in the short-term).
I purchased Sky TV earlier this year to watch the cricket world cup and
consequently pay a monthly fee. The introduction of a further fee to allow
me to watch (second rate) Premier League football matches and the other
sports I already receive will not be countenanced.
At the end of my existing agreement in 12 months' time my aerial will be
returned. Speaking to other subscribers, that is a common reaction.
P J R Baker,
17 Arne Grove, Horley
</TEXT>
