were also discovered at Bryant &amp; Co. Butte has launched legal action
claiming damages of Dollars 325m (Pounds 184m) from more than 70 former
executives and advisers, including Bryant &amp; Co. Also named in the Butte
litigation is Mr Clive Smith, the Midland's based entrepreneur with natural
resources interests, who helped bring Richmond and Butte to the market. Mr
Smith and his family interests held 11 per cent of Corporate Broking
Services, the defunct broker which sponsored the Richmond float.
